# Fit&Lead Design System

Welcome to the Fit&Lead component library and design system documentation.

## 🎨 Design System

This Storybook showcases a complete design system built for the Fit&Lead test assignment:

- **Design Tokens**: Colors, typography, spacing, and other design primitives
- **Components**: Reusable UI components (Button, Card)
- **Patterns**: Common UI patterns and layouts
- **Accessibility**: WCAG AA compliant components

## 🧩 Components

### Button
Versatile button component with 7 variants, 5 sizes, and multiple states.
- Variants: primary, secondary, ghost, danger, subtle, link, tonal
- Sizes: xs, sm, md, lg, xl
- States: default, hover, focus, disabled, loading
- Icons: left, right, or both

[View Button Stories →](/story/components-button--primary)

### Card
Flexible content card for benefits, features, and content grids.
- Variants: default, elevated, outlined
- Interactive: clickable links or buttons
- Customizable: with/without icons, configurable heading levels

[View Card Stories →](/story/components-card--default)

## 🎯 Design Tokens

### Colors
- **Primary**: #00484F (dark teal)
- **Accent**: #FBEA1B (yellow)
- **Neutrals**: 50-900 scale
- **Semantic**: success, warning, danger, info

### Typography
- **Font Family**: Public Sans
- **Scale**: xs (12px) to 4xl (46px)
- **Weights**: normal (400), medium (500), semibold (600), bold (700)

### Spacing
8px-based system: xs (8px), sm (16px), md (24px), lg (32px), xl (48px), 2xl (64px)

### Border Radius
sm (4px), md (6px), lg (8px), xl (10px), 2xl (32px), full (9999px - pill)

## 🚀 Tech Stack

- **Framework**: Next.js 15 (App Router)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v4
- **Language**: TypeScript
- **Component Docs**: Storybook 9
- **Testing**: Vitest (configured)

## 📖 Usage

All components are built with:
- ✅ Design tokens (no hardcoded values)
- ✅ Accessibility (ARIA, keyboard navigation)
- ✅ TypeScript (strict mode)
- ✅ SSR-safe (Next.js compatible)
- ✅ Theme support (light/dark mode ready)

